Experiment 5: Developing a Toggle Button
Aim
To design and develop a toggle button that switches between two states (ON/OFF) when clicked, using programming techniques.

Algorithm
1.Start the program.
2.Initialize the toggle button with a default state (e.g., OFF).
3.Display the toggle button on the screen.
4.Wait for the user to click or interact with the button.
5.When the button is clicked:
6.Check the current state of the button.
7.If the state is OFF, change it to ON.
8.If the state is ON, change it to OFF.
9.Update the button appearance/text based on the new state.
10.Repeat steps 4–6 until the program is terminated.
11.Stop the program.
